  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>

  <p>
    SafetyWing and Cigna Global serve different needs for different people at different life stages. The right choice depends entirely on what you actually need.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance</strong> is excellent travel medical insurance for young, healthy people who just need a safety net. At ~$45/month with no commitment, it's perfect for testing the nomad lifestyle. Don't expect healthcare—expect emergency rescue. If you're 28, perfectly healthy, and just want something in case you break your leg, SafetyWing Nomad delivers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is comprehensive health insurance for people who want to actually be insured. If you're over 40, have any health conditions, have a family, or simply want the security of knowing you're covered for anything, Cigna is the better choice. You pay 3-5x more because you get 3-5x more coverage. That's not a ripoff—it's a different product.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing Remote Health</strong> sits between them—real health insurance at a startup price point. Worth considering if you want comprehensive coverage but prefer SafetyWing's approach.
  </p>

  <p>
    The mistake is choosing SafetyWing Nomad thinking you're getting Cigna-level coverage at a bargain. You're not. Choose the product that matches your actual needs and risk tolerance.
  </p>

